docs.lead_paragraph: In the weeks since President Clinton announced the closing of Pennsylvania Avenue in front of the White House, tourists and native Washingtonians have had to make numerous adjustments. About 26,000 cars and trucks drove that part of Pennsylvania Avenue between 15th and 17th Streets every day. Now, traffic snakes out in all directions, clogging downtown streets and making drive-by tourism a thing of the past.

headline.main: White House Traffic Ban Earns Mixed Reviews
